World Stage Limited, a research and technology driven Africa focused firm is set to hold the annual WorldStage Economic Summit today both virtually (through Zoom) and physically at the IBIS Hotels, Ikeja, Lagos, Nigeria. According to a statement by the organizer, the objective of the hybrid WES 2022 with the theme, ‘Nigeria’s Economy: Bridging the infrastructural gap’ is to examine the infrastructural gap challenges and proffer solutions that would significantly help at improving prospects of achieving the nation’s economic potential. The statement said as major Nigerian political parties decide their presidential candidates for the 2023 general election, the Summit has strong expectations that the next administration will focus on bridging the multibillion dollar infrastructural gap in the country. The Acting Director-General of the Infrastructure Concession Regulatory Commission (ICRC), Mr. Micheal Ohiani is scheduled to deliver the keynote address at the Summit  while the lead paper will be delivered by Dr Oluseye Samuel Ajuwon, a lecturer/researcher in economics at the University of Lagos, Nigeria with PhD in Development Finance from the University of Stellenbosch Business School, South Africa. Participants from online are expected to register for participation in the summit scheduled for  Jun 22, 2022 10:00 AM West Central Africa  through https://us06web.zoom.us/meeting/register/tZYucu-rqjoqEtdNipetCe1B9e_hATARn8m9 . WES 2022 is the 6th in the series of 10 editions since WorldStage consolidated its economic conferences under the umbrella of an economic summit. WES is conceived to address economic challenges through diagnoses and application of practicable solutions with public and private sector engagement in a research and innovation driven platform to inspire new thinking in business initiative, policy formulation/implementation, economic reform and development. World Stage Limited is a research and technology driven Africa focused firm with expertise in multidimensional communication services that helps public and private organizations to realise their full potentials.